  "texts": [
    "We propose that judicious attention allocation is a moral skill.",
    "And so, if reliance on automated systems deprives us of opportunities to develop and exercise this skill, it may pose a moral problem even if these systems were otherwise assistive for discharging our duties of attention.",
    "We address both questions in Sect. 2.",
    "But first, we complete the groundwork for our critique by developing a conception of attention as a moral skill. 5",
    "For our purposes, understanding judicious attention allocation in terms of skill emphasizes three important points."
  ],
